FBIS4-37658 "drnes121_k_94009" FBIS-NES-94-121 Daily Report 22 Jun 1994 IRAQ Court Passes Amputation Sentences on Thieves Court Passes Amputation Sentences on Thieves JN2206191594 Baghdad Republic of Iraq Radio Network in Arabic 1800 GMT 22 Jun 94 JN2206191594 Baghdad Republic of Iraq Radio Network Arabic BFN [Text] The Diyala criminal court has passed hand amputation sentences on two culprits and ordered that a third partner be apprehended for the crime of stealing five carpets from the Buhruz al-Kabir Mosque in the Ba'qubah District on the night of 20 January 1994. The culprits are 'Aziz Sa'd Dahash, a 32-year-old employee; Nadir 'Ali Fulayyih, a 23-year-old soldier; and Faruq Ahmad, a 37- year-old retiree and fugitive. The perpetrators used a government vehicle belonging to the Water and Sewage Department of the Kan'an Subdistrict.
